In May 2009, members of the United States Cabinet and Obama administration officials traveled across the Midwest to visit auto communities and discuss federal recovery efforts for auto communities and workers. The officials included Secretary of the Interior Ken Salazar, Secretary of Agriculture Tom Vilsack, Secretary of Commerce Gary Locke, Secretary of Labor Hilda Solis, Secretary of Housing and Urban Development Shaun Donovan, Secretary of Transportation Ray LaHood, Secretary of Energy Steven Chu, Secretary of Education Arne Duncan, Environmental Protection Agency Administrator Lisa Jackson, Small Business Administrator Karen Mills, Associate Attorney General Tom Perrelli, and Dr. Ed Montgomery, the President's Director of Auto Recovery and Workers. They discussed immediate relief efforts and long-term economic revitalization for communities dependent on the auto and manufacturing industry. The events took place in Ohio, Michigan, Indiana, and Wisconsin.